1
00:00:02,920 --> 00:00:05,839
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:28,505
CONFESSION

3
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:33,552
[Yagami] Light, there's another message
from the Second Kira.

4
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:36,096
It was sent to Sakura TV
and we intercepted it.

5
00:01:36,471 --> 00:01:38,557
I'm told it's a video
and a journal this time.

6
00:01:38,974 --> 00:01:40,892
Anyway, I figured I should tell you.

7
00:01:41,435 --> 00:01:42,477
A journal?

8
00:01:42,686 --> 00:01:44,688
What is that idiot up to now?

9
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:46,888
Why can't he just wait?

10
00:01:51,111 --> 00:01:53,071
He wanted the journal shown on TV?

11
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,573
Yes. This is it.

12
00:01:55,574 --> 00:01:56,617
Hmm...

13
00:01:57,534 --> 00:01:59,119
2006?

14
00:01:59,494 --> 00:02:01,246
These entries are from last year.

15
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:04,166
Please take a look at the entry
he made on the 30th.

16
00:02:06,043 --> 00:02:08,670
[Light] "Confirmed our Shinigami
at the Tokyo Dome."

17
00:02:09,212 --> 00:02:12,966
This is probably supposed to mean
that he's going to do it on May 30th.

18
00:02:13,342 --> 00:02:14,676
If these were aired on TV,

19
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:17,387
his intentions would be obvious
to anyone who sees it.

20
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:19,306
[cackles]

21
00:02:19,389 --> 00:02:22,768
[Light] Besides, he can't see my Shinigami
unless he touches my Death Note.

22
00:02:22,893 --> 00:02:24,436
How's he planning to do that?

23
00:02:25,354 --> 00:02:28,273
22nd - My friend and I showed off
our notebooks in Aoyama.

24
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,318
[Misa] Hey, Rem.

25
00:02:31,443 --> 00:02:32,361
[Rem] Hmm?

26
00:02:32,736 --> 00:02:33,737
[Misa] I forget,

27
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:36,531
why can't I see my own lifespan
even though I have Shinigami eyes?

28
00:02:36,615 --> 00:02:37,532
MISA AMANE

29
00:02:37,616 --> 00:02:38,867
Do you think you could tell me again?

30
00:02:39,534 --> 00:02:41,536
Humans with Shinigami eyes

31
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:44,206
only need to know
the lifespan of their victims.

32
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:48,251
And just as we can't see
the lifespan of others of our kind,

33
00:02:48,418 --> 00:02:51,963
humans who possess a Death Note
cannot see each other's lifespan

34
00:02:52,089 --> 00:02:54,216
-even with the eyes.
-[Misa sighs]

35
00:02:56,009 --> 00:02:57,302
"May 22nd,

36
00:02:57,386 --> 00:03:00,097
my friend and I showed off
our notebooks in Aoyama."

37
00:03:00,222 --> 00:03:02,849
If by "notebooks" he is referring to
our Death Notes,

38
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:05,644
that's something
that could only be understood by me.

39
00:03:05,936 --> 00:03:09,439
And as for the police,
they'll be distracted by May 30th entry.

40
00:03:09,564 --> 00:03:13,610
"We confirmed our Shinigami
at the baseball game at the Tokyo Dome."

41
00:03:13,777 --> 00:03:15,654
It must have been intended for them.

42
00:03:16,113 --> 00:03:18,573
I'm almost positive
that the real message from this diary

43
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:20,534
is the one regarding Aoyama.

44
00:03:20,784 --> 00:03:22,494
But if that's the case…

45
00:03:23,829 --> 00:03:24,871
What do you think?

46
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,164
Is it real?

47
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:29,918
I have to be careful not to say too much.

48
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:32,671
Better to wait
and hear his opinion first.

49
00:03:33,505 --> 00:03:34,965
At this point in time,

50
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:37,050
all I can say for sure is
he must be stupid.

51
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:38,552
Yeah, I agree.

52
00:03:38,802 --> 00:03:42,013
I mean, it's completely obvious he wants
to meet Kira at the home game.

53
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:45,350
Doesn't he understand what would happen
if we aired this message?

54
00:03:45,559 --> 00:03:49,146
It would create an immediate panic
and the game would have to be canceled.

55
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:51,440
To be honest, it's so stupid.

56
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:54,693
[chewing] Mmm.
I'm not even sure

57
00:03:54,776 --> 00:03:57,320
how to deal
with this whole situation anymore.

58
00:03:58,321 --> 00:04:00,073
If we make the diary public,

59
00:04:00,157 --> 00:04:02,743
then we'll be forced to make
some kind of televised announcement

60
00:04:02,826 --> 00:04:04,578
cancelling the game on the 30th.

61
00:04:04,953 --> 00:04:06,246
But if we don't broadcast it,

62
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:08,790
we can be sure
the Second Kira won't do anything.

63
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:11,042
Won't cancelling the game make him angry?

64
00:04:11,126 --> 00:04:12,669
There's no telling what he'll do.

65
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:14,421
Frankly, that's not a big concern.

66
00:04:14,838 --> 00:04:16,715
From what we have witnessed
it's safe to say

67
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:18,592
the Second Kira admires the real one.

68
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:20,761
He gave his word to the Kira we invented

69
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:22,679
that he'd refrain from killing aimlessly.

70
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:24,222
I'm inclined to believe that.

71
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:26,975
I say we make it public

72
00:04:27,225 --> 00:04:29,519
and we air an announcement
canceling the game.

73
00:04:29,853 --> 00:04:31,104
At the same time, we'll announce

74
00:04:31,229 --> 00:04:33,148
that on May 30th
we're gonna set up checkpoints

75
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:35,442
on all roads leading to the Tokyo Dome.

76
00:04:36,485 --> 00:04:37,569
And finally,

77
00:04:37,736 --> 00:04:39,780
we'll send a response
from our invented Kira,

78
00:04:40,155 --> 00:04:43,325
something like "I understand,
and I agree to meet you there."

79
00:04:43,492 --> 00:04:46,578
Ryuzaki, you don't honestly expect
him to go there

80
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,538
if we set up checkpoints
around the Dome, do you?

81
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:51,666
I don't think that Kira
would even consider it,

82
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:53,585
but it's possible the other one might.

83
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:57,631
It all depends on how stupid he really is.

84
00:04:58,006 --> 00:05:01,384
However, assuming he is not
actually the idiot we think he is,

85
00:05:02,010 --> 00:05:05,472
there could be another message
hidden in this diary,

86
00:05:05,597 --> 00:05:07,432
one that's not so obvious.

87
00:05:07,974 --> 00:05:10,435
If there's a message here
written in some code

88
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:14,231
that only people with this Shinigami power
can understand,

89
00:05:14,356 --> 00:05:16,775
there would be no way for me
to decipher it.

90
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,068
Still, it would only make sense

91
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:21,238
for us to look into all of the places
that were mentioned in the journal.

92
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:24,741
Uh, 22nd,
he's meeting a friend in Aoyama.

93
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:29,204
The 24th,
meeting another friend in Shibuya.

94
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:32,833
We have to be prepared for the possibility
that all of our efforts will be fruitless.

95
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:35,961
Let's keep an eye out
for people with notebooks in Aoyama,

96
00:05:36,086 --> 00:05:38,338
and people in clothing stores in Shibuya.

97
00:05:39,673 --> 00:05:40,924
It's as I thought.

98
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:43,593
If this phony Kira skips up
and gets apprehended,

99
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:46,179
at the very least
I have to obtain his notebook.

100
00:05:46,263 --> 00:05:47,305
And in the worst-case scenario,

101
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:50,267
I may end up
having to kill everyone there.

102
00:05:50,976 --> 00:05:52,060
All we can do

103
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:54,813
is place more surveillance cameras
in Aoyama and Shibuya

104
00:05:54,938 --> 00:05:56,773
in the hopes that we might
capture something.

105
00:05:56,857 --> 00:05:58,900
We should also arrange to have
undercover officers

106
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:01,152
in both locations on these dates.

107
00:06:01,486 --> 00:06:03,446
I should probably go
to Aoyama and Shibuya

108
00:06:03,572 --> 00:06:05,365
since I blend in with the crowd there,
you know.

109
00:06:06,575 --> 00:06:07,576
[Light] I'll go too.

110
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:08,869
But Light…

111
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,954
I'll be all right. Don't worry.

112
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:13,498
Aoyama and Shibuya are places
I'd go anyway.

113
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:15,458
Not to mention, out of all of us

114
00:06:15,542 --> 00:06:18,503
I'd probably look the most natural
hanging out with Matsui there.

115
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:19,880
Besides,

116
00:06:20,005 --> 00:06:22,966
the Second Kira would be there
looking for Kira, not for the police.

117
00:06:26,845 --> 00:06:30,098
[Light] Okay, we will talk
more about our trips tomorrow.

118
00:06:30,932 --> 00:06:32,934
[Matsui] Sounds good, Light.
See you tomorrow.

119
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:34,311
Careful getting home

120
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,485
-[phone ringing]
-[Matsui] Huh?

121
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:44,821
It never fails.

122
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:46,948
The second I'm out the door,
my phone starts ringing.

123
00:06:47,032 --> 00:06:48,033
Yes?

124
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,409
[Ryuzaki] It's Ryuzaki.

125
00:06:49,826 --> 00:06:51,161
When you two are working together,

126
00:06:51,286 --> 00:06:53,747
I want you to keep a close eye on Light
the entire time.

127
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:55,957
And please keep this between you and me.

128
00:06:56,499 --> 00:06:57,751
Uh... sure.

129
00:06:58,043 --> 00:06:59,210
Yeah, I understand.

130
00:06:59,961 --> 00:07:00,879
[sighs]

131
00:07:01,296 --> 00:07:03,298
I guess he still plans
to investigate Light

132
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:05,842
until the probability that he's Kira
reaches zero.

133
00:07:08,053 --> 00:07:09,054
[Light] I'm home.

134
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:11,431
Hello, dear. You're back quite late today.

135
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:12,390
[Light] Yeah.

136
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:14,392
I'm supposed to keep the fact

137
00:07:14,517 --> 00:07:16,770
that I'm helping
with the Kira investigation a secret.

138
00:07:17,228 --> 00:07:19,773
It's because I was hanging out
with my girlfriend.

139
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:21,066
Your...

140
00:07:21,358 --> 00:07:22,567
[Sayu squeals] What?

141
00:07:22,776 --> 00:07:24,653
Light, you have a girlfriend now?
What's her name?

142
00:07:24,986 --> 00:07:28,114
It's not that surprising.
I'm 18 and I'm in university now.

143
00:07:28,198 --> 00:07:29,866
Of course I have a girlfriend.

144
00:07:29,991 --> 00:07:32,118
You should look for a boyfriend, Sayu.

145
00:07:32,535 --> 00:07:35,038
Huh? A boyfriend?
What's that supposed to mean?

146
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:37,415
Light, aren't you going
to have any dinner?

147
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:40,293
[Light] Actually, I’m still full
from room service at the hotel.

148
00:07:40,418 --> 00:07:43,171
[squeals] I can't believe
you just said that to mum.

149
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:45,924
So what's this about a hotel?
Sound pretty suspicious.

150
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:48,760
Okay, Ryuk.

151
00:07:49,386 --> 00:07:50,804
We need to have a little talk.

152
00:07:51,054 --> 00:07:52,639
Oh… Should have known

153
00:07:53,056 --> 00:07:55,475
And I'd appreciate an answer
if you could.

154
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:58,979
If two Shinigami happen to meet
in the human world,

155
00:07:59,145 --> 00:08:01,690
-are they allowed to speak to each other?
-Hard to say.

156
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,526
As long as I'm attached to a human,

157
00:08:04,609 --> 00:08:08,321
I'd say it's against the rules,
unless I have their permission first.

158
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:11,157
But there's no laws against it either,

159
00:08:11,366 --> 00:08:12,784
so I guess it's possible

160
00:08:12,951 --> 00:08:15,036
that another Shinigami might talk to me.

161
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:18,832
So does that mean if this fake Kira's
Shinigami were to see you,

162
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:21,251
there's a chance he might mention the fact
that you’re with me

163
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:22,669
and reveal that I'm Kira?

164
00:08:23,044 --> 00:08:26,214
[Ryuk] They probably wouldn't,
but it depends on their personality.

165
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:28,758
And if this kind of situation did arise,

166
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:31,136
I can assume that you'll act
the way you normally do?

167
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:32,470
[Ryuk] Yeah.

168
00:08:32,595 --> 00:08:35,015
Even if I see another human
with a Shinigami,

169
00:08:35,098 --> 00:08:36,516
I'm not gonna tell you.

170
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:39,769
Well, I definitely think
you've got the right approach.

171
00:08:40,061 --> 00:08:41,062
[Ryuk] Uh… Thanks.

172
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:43,440
Huh?

173
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:44,774
There's no way.

174
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:47,152
Did he really think this far ahead?

175
00:08:47,485 --> 00:08:48,486
What is it?

176
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:50,822
[Light] Aoyama is a big area.

177
00:08:50,989 --> 00:08:52,866
I was searching
for possible meeting places

178
00:08:52,991 --> 00:08:54,743
when I stumbled upon this...

179
00:08:55,285 --> 00:08:56,453
On the 22nd,

180
00:08:56,578 --> 00:09:00,165
there's a big event going on at the club
in Aoyama called the Note Blue

181
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:03,084
Aoyama, Blue Mountain.

182
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:05,086
"Note" and "blue." It's a code.

183
00:09:05,295 --> 00:09:08,089
[Ryuk] Well, well, if you ask me,
that's pretty elaborate.

184
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,842
He might be smarter than I thought...

185
00:09:11,509 --> 00:09:14,971
which means I will have to be
that much more careful from now on.

186
00:09:15,388 --> 00:09:18,850
In any case, this Note Blue place
is definitely worth checking out.

187
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:20,393
What's the point in going there,

188
00:09:20,477 --> 00:09:22,645
if you don't want him
to find out that you're Kira?

189
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:24,230
You really think it's worth the risk?

190
00:09:32,697 --> 00:09:35,200
[Matsui] Uh… Excuse me. Light?

191
00:09:35,450 --> 00:09:36,826
So, what's going on here?

192
00:09:36,993 --> 00:09:39,037
Oh, these are some of my friends
from school.

193
00:09:40,872 --> 00:09:41,998
[Matsui] Nice to meet you.

194
00:09:42,082 --> 00:09:43,541
[Light] This is my cousin Taro.

195
00:09:44,334 --> 00:09:47,337
It's his first time ever in Tokyo
and he wants to see Aoyama and Roppongi,

196
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:49,964
so I figured the least we could do
is show him a good time.

197
00:09:50,048 --> 00:09:51,049
I'm counting on you guys.

198
00:09:51,674 --> 00:09:54,427
Oh, yeah. He also told me
he is looking for a girlfriend.

199
00:09:54,552 --> 00:09:56,429
So, does anyone want to volunteer?

200
00:09:56,596 --> 00:09:58,640
-[laughter]
-Hey, I never said that!

201
00:10:00,892 --> 00:10:02,268
I'm impressed, Light.

202
00:10:02,894 --> 00:10:04,270
I doubt that anyone would ever suspect

203
00:10:04,354 --> 00:10:07,148
that there was a police detective
hanging around with these students.

204
00:10:10,735 --> 00:10:12,612
With all of us walking together like this,

205
00:10:12,695 --> 00:10:14,072
even if Ryuk is seen,

206
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:17,033
no one would be able to tell
which one of us he's following.

207
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:20,745
It's also a good defense
against L's surveillance cameras.

208
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,747
Not such a bad way to investigate, really.

209
00:10:23,498 --> 00:10:25,083
I just have to stay relaxed

210
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:27,919
and keep an eye on the entrance
of the Note Blue when it opens.

211
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:37,220
Found you!

212
00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:46,271
"Moon" Yagami, is it?

213
00:10:47,147 --> 00:10:49,983
You’re the only one
whose lifespan I can't see.

214
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:51,776
LIGHT YAGAMI

215
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:53,194
He's Kira! I can't believe it.

216
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:55,446
I never thought it would be
this easy to find him.

217
00:11:01,536 --> 00:11:03,413
All right, Rem. Time to go.

218
00:11:03,705 --> 00:11:06,708
Huh? You finally found him
and now you just want to leave?

219
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:09,669
[girl] Well, I can't go up to him
and say "Hi, Kira.

220
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:12,213
Nice to meet you.
I'm the one who sent you the messages"

221
00:11:12,297 --> 00:11:13,506
with all these people around.

222
00:11:14,132 --> 00:11:17,802
I know his name now,
so I can easily find out all about him.

223
00:11:18,303 --> 00:11:20,471
After all, it's such a unique name.

224
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:42,827
Yagami, Light - Birthdate: Feb 28, 1989
Height: 179cm - Weight: 54kg

225
00:11:42,911 --> 00:11:43,786
BLOOD TYPE: A

226
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,955
[Misa] Oh, it's written as "moon,"
but read as "Light."

227
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:47,790
Light Yagami.

228
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:51,044
Oh, he sure is amazing.
Look at all this stuff.

229
00:11:51,169 --> 00:11:52,629
He won the national tennis championship

230
00:11:52,754 --> 00:11:55,465
when he was in his second
and third years of junior high.

231
00:11:55,798 --> 00:11:57,634
He gave an address
as the freshman representative

232
00:11:57,717 --> 00:12:00,887
at this year's entrance ceremony
at To-oh University.

233
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:02,805
I can't find a picture of him,

234
00:12:02,931 --> 00:12:05,808
but there won't be anyone else
with the name like Light Yagami.

235
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:09,646
Who would have ever thought
that Kira would be so young and handsome.

236
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:12,315
Everything about him
is better than I imagined.

237
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:15,235
I can't believe how easy it was
to purchase this information.

238
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:17,445
The world sure is a scary place.

239
00:12:17,570 --> 00:12:19,239
I even know his home address now!

240
00:12:20,782 --> 00:12:22,450
[Aizawa] So we were there both days.

241
00:12:22,575 --> 00:12:24,244
In Aoyama on the 22nd

242
00:12:24,327 --> 00:12:25,954
and in Shibuya on the 24th.

243
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:28,539
And we observed nothing of significance
on either occasion.

244
00:12:28,957 --> 00:12:31,709
That leaves us with only
the Dome on the 30th.

245
00:12:32,794 --> 00:12:35,755
[Light] I didn't notice anyone
who looked suspicious at the Note Blue.

246
00:12:36,589 --> 00:12:38,341
Was he serious about the Dome?

247
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:40,176
[beeping]

248
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:42,262
[Watari] Ryuzaki, apparently Sakura TV

249
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:45,014
has just received another message
from the Second Kira.

250
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:48,685
It was postmarked on the 23rd.

251
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,730
[Second Kira] I am happy to say
that I have found Kira.

252
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:54,065
To all of the people

253
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:56,150
at the television station
and the police department,

254
00:12:56,234 --> 00:12:57,568
I want to thank you very much.

255
00:12:57,819 --> 00:12:58,903
[Light] Huh?

256
00:12:59,028 --> 00:13:00,488
I-- I-- Impossible!

257
00:13:00,989 --> 00:13:02,198
Where? In Aoyama?

258
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:03,992
His Shinigami...

259
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:06,869
It must have seen Ryuk
and picked me out of the crowd.

260
00:13:07,412 --> 00:13:10,748
No… No, there's no way he could have known
who Ryuk was attached to.

261
00:13:10,999 --> 00:13:13,543
I checked repeatedly
that no one was following me.

262
00:13:14,335 --> 00:13:15,628
If this is true,

263
00:13:15,712 --> 00:13:16,921
the only possible event

264
00:13:17,088 --> 00:13:19,716
that would correspond with this tape
being mailed on the 23rd,

265
00:13:19,841 --> 00:13:22,051
is the entry regarding Aoyama on 22nd.

266
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:25,179
The only ones from the task force
who went to Aoyama

267
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:26,764
are Matsuda and Light Yagami.

268
00:13:27,515 --> 00:13:29,809
Is Light really Kira after all?

269
00:13:30,101 --> 00:13:32,395
Still, there's no proof
it even happened in Aoyama.

270
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:34,564
This is a disaster if he found him.

271
00:13:34,814 --> 00:13:35,732
Yeah.

272
00:13:35,815 --> 00:13:39,068
It most likely means that the two Kiras
are now cooperating with each other

273
00:13:39,569 --> 00:13:42,280
At this point I don't think
we should jump to any conclusions.

274
00:13:42,405 --> 00:13:45,616
The Second Kira is only saying
that he found him, nothing more.

275
00:13:45,742 --> 00:13:47,869
He may not have made contact yet.

276
00:13:48,036 --> 00:13:49,245
[Yagami] Hmm...

277
00:13:49,746 --> 00:13:51,205
Now that's it come to this...

278
00:13:51,789 --> 00:13:53,041
[slurps]

279
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:55,668
...we have no choice
but to communicate as the police

280
00:13:55,752 --> 00:13:57,545
directly with the Second Kira.

281
00:13:57,837 --> 00:13:59,255
You want to send a message?

282
00:13:59,714 --> 00:14:00,715
Yes.

283
00:14:00,882 --> 00:14:03,843
The police need to reach out
to the copycat and offer him a deal.

284
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:07,263
We need to negotiate with him
to see if we can get Kira's real name.

285
00:14:08,139 --> 00:14:09,515
[chuckles]

286
00:14:09,766 --> 00:14:12,518
That's the last thing
you wanted to hear, right?

287
00:14:13,144 --> 00:14:14,354
[Light] This isn't good.

288
00:14:14,604 --> 00:14:17,440
I have no idea
how the Fake Kira will react to this,

289
00:14:17,607 --> 00:14:20,860
but I have no means of stopping the police
from sending this message.

290
00:14:22,070 --> 00:14:23,946
[man on TV]
If Kira doesn't yet know your name,

291
00:14:24,072 --> 00:14:26,908
it may not be too late for you,
provided you're willing to cooperate.

292
00:14:27,158 --> 00:14:30,036
Whatever you do, you must not
approach Kira out of curiosity.

293
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:31,412
Make no mistake.

294
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:33,706
Kira will kill you if you contact him.

295
00:14:33,915 --> 00:14:36,459
You will used and disposed of.

296
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:38,002
Consider your own life for a moment.

297
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:40,588
Yours, like every other life,
has an intrinsic value.

298
00:14:40,922 --> 00:14:43,007
Now is your chance
to right past wrongs

299
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:44,967
by sharing what you know about Kira.

300
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:49,013
Only you can help us
bring his reign of terror to an end.

301
00:14:52,141 --> 00:14:53,393
Where are you going?

302
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:55,144
To introduce myself.

303
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:56,604
[rings the doorbell]

304
00:14:57,188 --> 00:14:58,815
[Rem] So, this is what you meant.

305
00:14:59,232 --> 00:15:01,275
Oh, could that be your father?

306
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:02,318
Coming.

307
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:05,863
Welcome ho--

308
00:15:07,115 --> 00:15:08,074
Hi.

309
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:10,034
Hello and good evening.

310
00:15:10,118 --> 00:15:11,911
My name is Misa Amane.

311
00:15:12,036 --> 00:15:14,247
I just came by to give Light
an important notebook

312
00:15:14,372 --> 00:15:16,082
he left at school earlier today.

313
00:15:16,207 --> 00:15:18,835
C-- Could you wait here for a second?

314
00:15:19,502 --> 00:15:21,796
[Sayu calls out] Light!

315
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:24,924
Notebook? Could it be...?

316
00:15:33,641 --> 00:15:34,517
[door closes]

317
00:15:38,896 --> 00:15:40,523
[Misa] Um... Pleased to meet you.

318
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:42,358
I am Misa Amane.

319
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:45,820
I thought you might get worried
if you saw the message on TV.

320
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:49,490
I just couldn't take it anymore,
so I brought this... notebook.

321
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:51,242
[trembling breath]

322
00:15:51,409 --> 00:15:52,493
A Death Note…

323
00:16:00,251 --> 00:16:01,377
A Shinigami!

324
00:16:02,253 --> 00:16:04,213
She's the Fake Kira.

325
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:06,757
-Huh?
-[Light] Please, come in.

326
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:08,759
[Misa] Uh, you're sure it's okay?

327
00:16:08,885 --> 00:16:10,094
Thanks.

328
00:16:10,261 --> 00:16:12,722
[Light] Mom, she came all this way
to return my notebook to me.

329
00:16:12,805 --> 00:16:14,640
Could you make us some tea?

330
00:16:14,891 --> 00:16:16,726
Sure, I don't see why not.

331
00:16:16,851 --> 00:16:18,186
-[Sayu] Huh?
-[Light] Hm?

332
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:19,729
I already told you about her.

333
00:16:20,313 --> 00:16:21,481
[Sachiko and Sayu] Huh?

334
00:16:25,234 --> 00:16:26,277
[Light] Have a seat.

335
00:16:27,612 --> 00:16:29,614
Oh... Um... thank you.

336
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:41,626
How did you find me?

337
00:16:42,210 --> 00:16:43,794
Oh… I knew it.

338
00:16:43,878 --> 00:16:46,422
You never made the Shinigami eye deal.

339
00:16:47,048 --> 00:16:49,300
When you have the Shinigami eyes,
like I do,

340
00:16:49,425 --> 00:16:52,428
you can see most people's
name and lifespan just by looking at them.

341
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:56,766
However, you can't see the lifespan
of any person who possesses a Death Note.

342
00:16:58,559 --> 00:16:59,810
No kidding.

343
00:16:59,936 --> 00:17:03,397
I have to admit, even I wasn't aware
of that little detail.

344
00:17:03,731 --> 00:17:05,775
Well, now you've managed to find me.

345
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:08,861
But you were careless.
What if you'd been caught by the police?

346
00:17:09,028 --> 00:17:11,030
Then they'd know everything about Kira.

347
00:17:11,489 --> 00:17:12,657
It's all right.

348
00:17:12,949 --> 00:17:14,825
Because the police didn't catch me.

349
00:17:14,951 --> 00:17:17,995
And if I do as you say from now on,
they will never be able to.

350
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:19,121
So we're safe.

351
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:22,083
After all, don't you need
someone to see L's name?

352
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:25,086
If you want, I could be your eyes.

353
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:26,671
So…

354
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:28,631
[Light] Yeah?

355
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:30,633
So what?

356
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:33,219
Would you please make me your girlfriend?

357
00:17:33,386 --> 00:17:34,262
Huh?

358
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:36,222
Girlfriend?

359
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:38,015
Yes.

360
00:17:38,391 --> 00:17:39,809
[Ryuk chuckles]

361
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:42,395
If she finds out I'm manipulating her
and gets hurt,

362
00:17:42,562 --> 00:17:43,896
she'll probably kill me.

363
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:45,231
But still...

364
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:46,691
Impossible.

365
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,442
The day you and I were in Aoyama,

366
00:17:48,568 --> 00:17:51,320
there were three times the usual number
of surveillance cameras around.

367
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:55,616
Anyone who was in Aoyama on the 22nd
would've definitely been caught on camera.

368
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:56,993
That includes me.

369
00:17:57,702 --> 00:18:00,162
If you and I were seen together,
it wouldn't look very good.

370
00:18:00,288 --> 00:18:02,498
In fact, even being here together
right now

371
00:18:02,582 --> 00:18:03,541
is a problem.

372
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:05,334
I wish you'd understand that.

373
00:18:05,543 --> 00:18:06,586
But look.

374
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:10,172
These are pictures of me
when I went to Aoyama that day.

375
00:18:12,174 --> 00:18:14,760
Well, I'm sure no one
would recognize her from this.

376
00:18:15,219 --> 00:18:17,221
And what about your fingerprints?

377
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:19,682
All those tapes you sent
to the TV station.

378
00:18:19,765 --> 00:18:21,892
They all had
the same fingerprints on them.

379
00:18:22,226 --> 00:18:24,145
Yeah, but those aren't my fingerprints.

380
00:18:24,395 --> 00:18:27,064
It's not like I do these things
without thinking about them first.

381
00:18:27,607 --> 00:18:30,276
Up until recently
I lived in the Kansai region.

382
00:18:30,401 --> 00:18:32,528
And I had this friend
who was into the occult.

383
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:35,698
I suggested that we distribute
this fake poltergeist video

384
00:18:35,865 --> 00:18:38,242
I had made
to a bunch of different TV shows,

385
00:18:38,367 --> 00:18:39,410
sort of as a prank.

386
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:41,370
And she agreed to help me with it.

387
00:18:41,454 --> 00:18:43,331
I had her take care of
all of the dubbing

388
00:18:43,456 --> 00:18:45,458
so my fingerprints
wouldn't be on the tapes.

389
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:47,209
Then I took them from her,

390
00:18:47,293 --> 00:18:48,544
added the Kira graphic

391
00:18:48,711 --> 00:18:51,088
and recorded the message
with that voice effect.

392
00:18:51,922 --> 00:18:54,550
And this friend you made the tapes with,
where is she now?

393
00:18:54,634 --> 00:18:55,718
Why you're doing this to me?

394
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:58,220
If you want me to kill her,
just say so and I'll kill her!

395
00:19:00,598 --> 00:19:02,642
If you really still can't trust me...

396
00:19:03,017 --> 00:19:06,228
then here, I'll even let you
hold on to my Death Note.

397
00:19:06,354 --> 00:19:08,022
But you'll just be holding it.

398
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:10,024
So, I'd still be the rightful owner of it

399
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:12,276
and that means
I get to keep my Shinigami eyes.

400
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:13,611
Isn't that right, Rem?

401
00:19:14,612 --> 00:19:15,863
Yes, that's right.

402
00:19:17,365 --> 00:19:19,700
Now, there's no way
I could possibly kill you.

403
00:19:20,284 --> 00:19:21,911
And if I become a burden to you

404
00:19:22,036 --> 00:19:23,788
then you can just kill me, okay?

405
00:19:24,664 --> 00:19:26,415
Why would she go this far?

406
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:30,586
But you might have removed
several pages from your Death Note.

407
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:33,339
You could be hiding them somewhere,
for all I know.

408
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:35,800
Why are you so suspicious of me?

409
00:19:36,092 --> 00:19:37,259
I already told you!

410
00:19:37,343 --> 00:19:39,595
I don't care, even if all you do
is use me.

411
00:19:39,762 --> 00:19:40,763
Believe me.

412
00:19:42,264 --> 00:19:43,933
[Light] How can you say that?

413
00:19:44,058 --> 00:19:45,309
Oh...

414
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:47,645
Exactly one year ago,

415
00:19:47,728 --> 00:19:49,772
my parents were killed in a robbery.

416
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:52,692
I was home with them at the time.
It happened right in front of me.

417
00:19:53,651 --> 00:19:55,945
I wanted that man
to pay for what he did.

418
00:19:56,362 --> 00:19:58,197
But the trial dragged on forever.

419
00:19:58,364 --> 00:20:01,492
Opinions started surfacing
that he was being falsely accused.

420
00:20:01,701 --> 00:20:03,035
Then it happened.

421
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:05,621
Kira punished him
for what he did to my parents.

422
00:20:06,122 --> 00:20:08,457
And that's why Kira means everything.

423
00:20:08,999 --> 00:20:11,001
Kira means everything to me.

424
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:13,170
All I...

425
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:16,132
All I wanted was the chance
to meet you one day.

426
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:18,884
So, I could thank you for what you did.

427
00:20:19,385 --> 00:20:20,636
[Misa sobs]

428
00:20:22,805 --> 00:20:24,807
So, all these irrational moves

429
00:20:24,974 --> 00:20:27,101
they're just he means for her
to meet Kira.

430
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:30,312
Still, she got around surveillance cameras
with ease

431
00:20:30,438 --> 00:20:33,107
and managed not to leave her fingerprints
on the evidence.

432
00:20:33,441 --> 00:20:35,109
She's not as stupid as I thought.

433
00:20:35,526 --> 00:20:38,028
And she has promised
to obey me from now on.

434
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:48,748
Huh?

435
00:20:54,462 --> 00:20:57,214
[breath trembling]

436
00:20:59,508 --> 00:21:00,593
I understand.

437
00:21:00,968 --> 00:21:02,428
I can't be your boyfriend, but...

438
00:21:02,636 --> 00:21:03,846
I can act like it.

439
00:21:04,346 --> 00:21:06,807
The lengths you went to meet me,
to be of help to me,

440
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:08,392
those eyes of yours

441
00:21:08,517 --> 00:21:10,519
that you sacrificed half your life to get,

442
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:12,480
will become my weapon.

443
00:21:13,731 --> 00:21:14,732
Thank you so much.

444
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:18,110
I'll try my hardest to make you love me.
I promise.

445
00:21:30,506 --> 00:21:36,505
TO BE CONTINUED

446
00:21:41,842 --> 00:21:45,805
[theme music plays]
